The paper focuses on convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification and object detection. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of specialized convolutional kernels for each example, which involves learning and optimization, indicating that it may also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to increase the size and capacity of a network while maintaining efficient inference, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach on classification and detection tasks, which could be related to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
